records.addlTxt:
1:30 PM Defendant Samantha L Young in court.  Attorney Gary J. Kryshak in court for Samantha L Young.  Attorney Jennifer C Zima in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Deputy Christianson is sworn in and testifies. Testifies to being dispatched to a residence for the report of a disturbance. Testifies to making contact w/ the defendant. Witness identifies the defendant in court, court recognizes. Testifies to the defendant stating there was a disturbance between her and her boyfriend and what it was about. Witness testifies to the defendant stating she had RS pinned down and why. Testifies speaking to JHY and gives the statements made by JHY. Testifies to the statements made by RS. Testifies to how RS was able to get away from the defendant. Testifies to RS not giving consent to the defendant to cut him with the knife. Testifies to the size of the knife. Testifies to the defendants statement regarding the knife incident. 
Attorney Kryshak cross examines the witness. Witness testifies to the defendant stating she was fearful of RS. Testifies to scratch marks seen on the defendant. Testifies to RS being smaller than the defendant. Testifies to the defendant stating she was protecting herself.
Attorney Kryshak argues he doesn't find probable cause for battery.
Court finds probable cause to believe a felony was committed and the defendant committed it.
Bond is continued. Not guilty pleas are entered.
Final pre-trial scheduled for November 11, 2022 at 11:00 am.
